    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Aim With this retrospective study, the investigators would like to evaluate and, if possible
      confirm, whether earlier revalvulation of the right ventricular outflow tract is better than
      late revalvulation. Up to now, no analysis is done to validate this policy change.

      Patient selection All patients registered in the database of paediatric and congenital
      cardiology of the University Hospitals in Leuven, with sufficient follow-up data, and who
      underwent transannular patching at repair will be included in the study.

      Methodology and statistical analysis All files will be reviewed for demographic,
      electrocardiographic, echocardiographic, and outcome data. Besides descriptive statistics,
      Cox regression will be performed to detect whether the time period between repair and
      revalvulation influences clinical outcome (defined as death, heart failure hospitalization,
      redo-revalvulation, implantation of automatic defibrillator, endocarditis).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
